        {
            "_id": "eWwvulvAEpgjwEtv",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Living Facade",
            "sort": 600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The carrion angel hides their true appearance behind a potent illusion that makes them appear as they did in life. The carrion angel has an automatic result of 42 on Deception checks and DCs to pass as living. While Living Facade is in effect, the carrion angel loses void healing and can be healed as if they were alive. This illusion lasts until the start of the carrion angel's next turn, but the angel can Sustain it indefinitely—when the carrion angel chooses to stop Sustaining it, they cannot use Living Facade again for 24 hours. The carrion angel's blasphemous stench aura is suppressed for as long as they maintain their Living Facade.</p>"
                },
